<HL>
   Business Brief -- American Recreation Centers Inc.:
   Purchase of 400,000 Shares
   By ESOP Cleared by Board
</HL>
<DATE>
12/31/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   AMRC LABOR
</CO>
<IN>
RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)
</IN>
<LP>
   American Recreation Centers Inc. said its board authorized
the purchase of 400,000 shares by its Employee Stock
Ownership Plan.
   The transaction was financed by a loan to the employee
organization from the company and will be repaid over five
years from annual contributions made to the organization by
the company. The company said it used its credit line to
secure the loan.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Sacramento, Calif., company said it purchases stock
for its members from time to time on the open market and
added that it will continue to do so.
   American Recreation Centers owns 22 bowling centers in
California and five in Texas. It also owns Right Start
Catalog Inc., a direct marketer of products for infants and
children.
</TEXT>
